data.description: Introduction to the ancient world from origins of human culture to the beginnings of written history as revealed by archaeological research at great sites and ruins around the globe. Archaeological analyses of important sites as case studies to illustrate concepts and techniques used by archaeologists in their efforts to understand the diversity of the human past.
data.title: ARCHAEOLOGY AND THE PREHISTORIC WORLD

data.description: Worldwide archaeological evidence for the development of human culture and behavior from the earliest appearance of human groups to the threshold of the agricultural revolution.
data.title: THE EMERGENCE OF HUMAN CULTURE
